body_html: At present, TensorFlow only supports primitive NumPy datatypes. If you need to represent a tensor of a tuple of values, you can instead use a (Python) tuple of tensors (see e.g. the tf.QueueBase documentation for an example).

body: At present, TensorFlow only supports primitive NumPy datatypes. If you need to represent a tensor of a tuple of values, you can instead use a (Python) tuple of tensors (see e.g. the [`tf.QueueBase`](https://www.tensorflow.org/versions/r0.7/api_docs/python/io_ops.html#QueueBase) documentation for an example).
